commit.message:
prune.exp (prune_gcc_output): Prune "could not create compact unwind for" warnings.

gcc:
2011-03-21  Jack Howarth  <howarth@bromo.med.uc.edu>

	* lib/prune.exp (prune_gcc_output): Prune "could not create
	compact unwind for" warnings.

libstdc++:
2011-03-21  Jack Howarth  <howarth@bromo.med.uc.edu>

	* testsuite/lib/prune.exp (libstdc++-dg-prune): Prune "could not
	create compact unwind for" warnings.

From-SVN: r171263

files.patch:
@@ -1,3 +1,8 @@
+2011-03-21  Jack Howarth  <howarth@bromo.med.uc.edu>
+
+	* lib/prune.exp (prune_gcc_output): Prune "could not create
+	compact unwind for" warnings.
+
 2011-03-20  Jakub Jelinek  <jakub@redhat.com>
 
 	PR c/42544

@@ -56,7 +56,10 @@ proc prune_gcc_output { text } {
     regsub -all "(^|
)\[^
\]*ld: warning: can't add line info to anonymous symbol\[^
\]*" $text "" text
     regsub -all "(^|
)\[^
\]*warning: DWARFDebugInfoEntry::AppendDependants\[^
\]*AT_\[^
\]*_bound\[^
\]*FORM_ref4\[^
\]*" $text "" text
     regsub -all "(^|
)\[^
\]*warning:\[^
\]*TAG_variable:  AT_location\[^
\]*didn't have valid function low pc\[^
\]*" $text "" text
-    
+
+    # Ignore harmless warnings from Xcode 4.0.
+    regsub -all "(^|
)\[^
\]*ld: warning: could not create compact unwind for\[^
\]*" $text "" text
+
     #send_user "After:$text
"
 
     return $text
